warning[W10007]: issue with attribute value
  ┌─ tests/move_check/warning_suppression/expect_all.move:3:10
  │
3 │ #[expect(all)]
  │          ^^^ 'all' matches multiple diagnostics, but 'expect' may only be used for individual diagnostics
  │
  = Use '#[allow(all)]' instead

warning[W09002]: unused variable
  ┌─ tests/move_check/warning_suppression/expect_all.move:4:26
  │
4 │ module 0x42::m { fun var(a: u64) { } }
  │                          ^ Unused parameter 'a'. Consider removing or prefixing with an underscore: '_a'
  │
  = This warning can be suppressed with '#[allow(unused_variable)]' applied to the 'module' or module member ('const', 'fun', or 'struct')

